This paper discusses the implementation of similarity search applications using distance functions and metric index structures. These topics are commonly studied in the fields of databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions applications related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), which further support these potential sub-categories.
